1. Install the package arc-gtk-theme or canta-gtk-theme-git (AUR) or layan-gtk-theme-git (AUR) or orchis-theme or

	 whitesur-cursor-theme-git whitesur-gtk-theme-git whitesur-icon-theme
	 
2. Put in /etc/environment the value

    GTK_THEME=WhiteSur-Dark-blue

3. Set the commands

    gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme WhiteSur-Dark-blue
    gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface color-scheme prefer-dark
    gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface cursor-theme WhiteSur-cursors
    gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface icon-theme WhiteSur-Dark

4. Put in ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini the lines

	[Settings]
	gtk-icon-theme-name = WhiteSur-Dark
	gtk-theme-name = WhiteSur-Dark-blue
	gtk-cursor-theme-name = WhiteSur-cursors
	gtk-application-prefer-dark-theme = true
